# Git authorship (VoxLane)

This repository belongs to **Radin Reanula** only. Cursor must **never** appear in GitHub authorship, contributor lists, or commit metadata.

Remote: `https://github.com/RadinReanula/VoxLane.git`

## Hard rules

- **Never** add `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>` (or any Cursor co-author trailer) to commit messages.
- **Never** add Cursor as a collaborator, contributor, author, or committer on commits, PRs, or releases.
- **Never** use `git commit --trailer` (or equivalent) to attach Cursor attribution.
- **Never** use plain `git commit` from PowerShell or Cursor's integrated shell on Windows — the environment may inject co-author trailers without asking.
- Commits must list **only** the user's identity as author and committer unless the user explicitly names another human co-author.

## Required commit workflow (Windows)

When the agent creates any commit for this repo:

1. Stage files with Git's native binary:
   - `"C:\Program Files\Git\mingw64\bin\git.exe" add ...`
2. Create the commit with **full control over the message body** using one of:
   - `commit-tree` via Git Bash (preferred), or
   - `"C:\Program Files\Git\mingw64\bin\git.exe" commit -F <message-file>` where the message file contains **only** the intended text (no trailers).
3. **Verify before push** — all of these must pass:
   - `git log -1 --format=%B` contains no `Co-authored-by`, `cursoragent`, or `cursor.com`
   - `git log -1 --format="%an <%ae>"` and `%cn <%ce>` are the user's identity only
4. Push only after verification succeeds.

## When pushing to GitHub

- Push only commits that pass the checks above.
- If co-author trailers appear after a commit, **do not push**. Rewrite the commit (e.g. `commit-tree`) and verify again.
- If history must be rewritten to remove Cursor attribution, do so before pushing and confirm with `git log --format=%B` across all commits on `main`.

## If contributor attribution is wrong on GitHub

Do not add more commits hoping GitHub will fix it. Rewrite local history without Cursor metadata, then force-push only when the user has asked for it or the branch has never been shared.
